{{ja-noun|なべ}}

# a broad-bottomed [[pot]] or [[pan]]
#: This term is less specific than English {{m|en|pot}} or {{m|en|pan}}, and can often be used to refer to either of these. The sample images at right illustrate some of the various items that can be called a ''nabe'' in Japanese.
# short for {{l|ja|鍋物|tr=''nabemono''}}, a [[dish]] where everything is cooked together in a ''nabe''; compare English {{m|en|hot pot}} or {{m|en|hotdish}}
#: ⇒ {{l|ja|鍋物|tr=''nabemono''}}
# by extension from the sense of someone working with pots and pans, a [[maidservant]]
#: ⇒ {{l|ja|御鍋|tr=''onabe''}}
